# SECTION 3: MODAL DEPLOYMENT PROTOCOL (CRITICAL)

## ⚠️ BEFORE ANY DEPLOYMENT

```python
def before_modal_deploy():
    """ALWAYS run this check before deploying"""
    
    # Step 1: Check existing apps
    # Run: modal app list
    
    existing_apps = count_modal_apps()
    
    if existing_apps > 1:
        return "❌ BLOCKED: Multiple apps running. Clean up first."
    
    if existing_apps == 1 and app_name != "ghl-omni-automation":
        return "⚠️ WARNING: Wrong app name. Should be ghl-omni-automation"
    
    return "✅ Safe to deploy"
```

## ✅ CORRECT Deployment

```bash
# Step 1: Check what exists
modal app list

# Step 2: If multiple apps, stop extras
modal app stop [old-app-name]

# Step 3: Deploy with --force
python -m modal deploy deploy.py --force

# Step 4: Verify (wait 5 min)
modal app list  # Should show ONLY ghl-omni-automation

# Step 5: Check scheduled functions running
# Modal dashboard → ghl-omni-automation → Check call counts
# keep_warm: Should show >0 calls after 5 min
```

## ❌ NEVER Do This

```bash
# DON'T deploy without checking apps first
python -m modal deploy deploy.py  # WRONG

# DON'T leave test apps running
# DON'T forget --force flag
# DON'T deploy multiple apps
```

## 📊 Post-Deployment Verification

```markdown
□ Wait 5 minutes
□ modal app list shows ONLY 1 app
□ keep_warm shows >0 calls
□ Wait 30 minutes  
□ outreach functions showing calls
□ Dashboard loads in <2 seconds
```

